      <title>Girls Trapped in Cycle of Servitude at Pakistan’s Brick Kilns</title>
      <category domain="https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/education/">Education</category>
      <pubDate>Tue, 17 Jan 2017 14:41:19 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Mahwish Qayyum</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/articles/2017/01/17/girls-trapped-cycle-servitude-pakistans-brick-kilns</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/articles/2017/01/17/girls-trapped-cycle-servitude-pakistans-brick-kilns</guid>
      <description>Driven by poverty and lack of education, hundreds of thousands of Pakistanis are forced to take loans from brick kiln owners and spend a lifetime working off what they owe. The debt then usually passes on to their children, even to girls as young as five years old.</description>
